How the navigation works

If you only have a few pages the top bar navigation will serve you well, but if you have a lot of pages you need to structure them in a way your visitors can easily navigate.

In this section we have created a deep structure of pages - this allow you to drill down a long chain of pages and see how the navigation bars at the top and side serve your needs.

Start editing content

If you want to edit this website, you need to log in to the C1 CMS Console.

To open the console:

  1. Append "/Composite" to this website base URL and press Enter, or click the link below:

    Start editing: Launch the C1 CMS Console


  2. Click "Start" on the page that opens.
  3. In the login form, enter your username and password.
    Your username/password was specified by the admin setting up this site.

You will log in to the console defaulting to the Content perspective. Here, expand "Websites" and the front page below and select the page you want to edit.

C1 CMS is a web content management system running on Microsoft's .NET platform - ideal for integration and expansion.

Being both open source and backed by commercial support, add-ons and product warranty this top rated CMS is ideal for building company websites.

A mobile first starter site.

This starter site is based on Bootstrap - the most popular front-end framework for developing responsive, mobile first projects on the web.

All styling is handled with LESS - a CSS pre-processor, meaning that it extends the CSS language, adding features that allow variables, mixins, functions and many other techniques that allow you to make CSS that is more maintainable, themable and extendable.

About us

In short we are 150+ passionate people. Who love the web. Going to work everyday with the goal of creating fantastic software.

We strive to deliver quality in software and tooling for users and developers. We believe in open standards, unobstructive frameworks and the power of skilled humans, be it developers, designers or users.

Test components

In this section we have created a set of pages which enable you to see how your website behave in terms of design and navigation.

We have used a few components that allows you to quickly add images and play videos, show content in image and icon teasers.

We hope this will save you some time to quickly identify if your selections of colors, changes to layout, navigation settings etc. behave as you would expect.
